VIDEO | Hindi language row: Addressing a press conference in Mumbai on the eve of monsoon session of state legislature, Maharashtra CM Devendra Fadnavis (
@Dev_Fadnavis
) says, "When Uddhav Thackeray was the Chief Minister, he had accepted the Mashelkar panel's suggestions on implementing three-language policy - Marathi, Hindi and English - from class 1. His cabinet had accepted the panel's suggestion, but he is doing politics now. We have already clarified that Marathi would remain compulsory. They are only protesting against Hindi, but they have accepted English."

(Full video available on PTI Videos - 
ptivideos.com)

